==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Informality
<hw>In`for*mal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Informalities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being informal; lack of regular, prescribed, or customary form;
<as>as, the <ex>informality</ex> of legal proceedings</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An informal, unconventional, or unofficial act or
proceeding; something which is not in proper or prescribed form or does
not conform to the established rule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Informally</ent>⟦br⟧
